'Cation_ATPase_N' => 'SM00831____Cation transporter/ATPase, N-terminus____This entry represents the conserved N-terminal region found in several classes of cation-transporting P-type ATPases, including those that transport H+, Na+, Ca2+, Na+/K+, and H+/K+. In the H+/K+- and Na+/K+-exchange P-ATPases, this domain is found in the catalytic alpha chain. In gastric H+/K+-ATPases, this domain undergoes reversible sequential phosphorylation inducing conformational changes that may be important for regulating the function of these ATPases PUBMED:12480547, PUBMED:12529322.',
