'EPEND' => 'SM00026____Ependymins____ Ependymins are the predominant proteins in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) of teleost fish. They have been implicated in the neurochemistry of memory and neuronal regeneration. They are glycoproteins of about 200 amino acids that can bind calcium. Four cysteines are conserved that probably form disulfide bonds.',
