'MR_MLE' => 'SM00922____Mandelate racemase / muconate lactonizing enzyme, C-terminal domain____Mandelate racemase (MR) and muconate lactonizing enzyme (MLE) are two bacterial enzymes involved in aromatic acid catabolism. They catalyze mechanistically distinct reactions yet they are related at the level of their primary, quaternary (homooctamer) and tertiary structures PUBMED:2215699, PUBMED:8256284. This entry represents the C-terminal region of these proteins.',
